-- Deutsche Bank Said to Hire Michael Lam From Credit Suisse for Asian Debt
-- Katrina Nicholas
-- 2010-06-18T08:03:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/deutsche-bank-said-to-hire-michael-lam-from-credit-suisse-for-asian-debt.html

          
          
             Deutsche Bank AG  hired  Michael Lam 
from Credit Suisse Group AG to be head of North Asia debt
capital markets origination, according to two people familiar
with the matter.  
 Lam, who will be based in Hong Kong, will report to  Patrick Tsang , one of the people said, asking not to be identified as
the matter is private.  
 David Greenbaum  has transferred from the German bankâ€™s New
York office to Singapore, where he will head South Asia debt
capital markets origination, the person said.  
 Deutsche Bank spokesman  Mark Bennewith  and Credit Suisse
spokesman  Adam Harper  declined to comment. Lam, who has yet to
start with Deutsche Bank, also declined to comment when
contacted by telephone in Hong Kong.  
